  abstract =    {
Using the Cadence SMV symbolic model checker we synthesize, under certain error
assumptions, a scheduler for the smart card personalization system, a case
study that has been proposed by Cybernetix Recherche in the context of the
EU IST project AMETIST.  The controller that we synthesize, and of which we
prove optimality, has been previously patented.  Due to the large number of
states (which is beyond $10^{13}$), this synthesis problem appears to be out of
the scope of existing tools for controller synthesis, which typically use some
form of explicit state enumeration.  Our result provides new evidence that
model checkers can be useful to tackle industrial sized problems in the area of
scheduling and control synthesis.
}
}

